<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="285" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,258,1003]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,330,355]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">Etymology.</emphasis>
The “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grismado &amp; Carrión" authorityYear="2017" box="[402,469,330,355]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Almafuerte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facon">facón</taxonomicName>
” is a knife (used as tool and as weapon) by the gauchos. The specific epithet refers to the straight and acute shape of the ventral branch of the RTA in retrolateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="285" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,258,1003]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,402,427]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grismado &amp; Carrión" authorityYear="2017" box="[470,564,403,427]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Almafuerte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facon">
<emphasis box="[470,564,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">A. facon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar in the RTA, and the general shape of the bulb to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grismado &amp; Carrión" authorityYear="2017" box="[1304,1436,402,427]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Almafuerte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis box="[1304,1436,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">A. goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the ventral protrusion of the ventral part of tegulum is less pronounced. Other differences from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grismado &amp; Carrión" authorityYear="2017" box="[1264,1395,438,463]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Almafuerte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis box="[1264,1395,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">A. goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the more straight ventral branch of the RTA (in retrolateral view), and the absence of a distal ventral retrolateral ledge on the palpal patella (
<figureCitation box="[460,560,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1465,1487]" captionTargetBox="[168,1405,208,1439]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1443]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 20. Almafuerte spp. genitalia, a – d, Almafuerte goloboffi, sp. nov.; a − b, male holotype; c, female from Termas del Palmar (paratype MACN-Ar 35565); d, female from El Hongo (paratype MACN-Ar 10771); e − f, Almafuerte facon, sp. nov., male holotype; g − h, Almafuerte vigorosa, sp. nov., male holotype. a, e, g, left palp, ventral view; b, f, h, same, retrolateral view; c, d, vulvae, cleared, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1036151/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">Fig. 20 f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="285" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,258,1003]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,546,571]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[354,517,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">
Male 
<typeStatus box="[420,517,546,571]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
: Measurements: Total length 8.22, carapace 4.02 long, 3.08 wide; sternum 2.11 long, 1.64 wide. Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.152, ALE 0.171, PME 0.162, PLE 0.139; AME-AME 0.128, AME-ALE 0.0293, PME-PME 0.0767, PME-PLE 0.259, ALE-PLE 0.158. Legs (femur/patella/tibia/metatarsus/ tarsus); I 2.74/1.73/2.08/1.57/1.02, II 2.46/1.54/1.78/1.47/0.989, III 2.15/1.13/1.32/1.55/0.99, IV 2.79/1.54/2.06/ 2.22/1.02. Leg spination: femora: I d1-1, p0-0-0/1-1; II d1-1-0, pd 0-1-1; III d1-1, pd 1-1-0-0/1, rd 0-1-1; IV d1-1, p1, r0-0-1-1; patellae: III r1, IV r1; tibiae: I p0-0-1, 
<date box="[742,795,727,751]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">v2-2</date>
-2ap, II p1-1-1(right), 1-0-1-1 (left), 
<date box="[1209,1260,727,751]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">v2-2</date>
-2ap III d1-0-0, p1-0-1-1, 
<date box="[263,316,763,787]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">v2-2</date>
-2ap, r1-1; IV p1-0-1 (right) 1-1-1 (left, not paired), 
<date box="[906,959,763,787]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">v2-2</date>
-0-2ap, r1-1-0-1(right) 1-1 (left); metatarsi I p0-1-1, 
<date box="[255,309,799,823]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">v2-2</date>
, r0-0-1; II p0-1-1, 
<date box="[517,571,799,823]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">v2-2</date>
, r0-0-1; III d2-2-2, p0-1-1, 
<date box="[877,930,799,823]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">v2-2</date>
-2ap, r0-1-1; IV d2-2-2, p0-1-1, 
<date box="[1289,1341,799,823]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">v2-2</date>
-2ap, r0- 1-1. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[271,415,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1895]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 19. Almafuerte spp. a – e, Almafuerte facon, sp. nov., male holotype; f – j, Almafuerte vigorosa, sp. nov., male holotype. a, f, habitus dorsal; b, g, same, ventral; c, h, left palp, retrolateral view; d, i, same, ventral; e, j, detail of RTA." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1036149/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">Figs. 19 c–e</figureCitation>
; 20 e–f): similar to that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grismado &amp; Carrión" authorityYear="2017" box="[696,830,834,859]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Almafuerte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis box="[696,830,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">A. goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except by the differences above described. All other characters are common for the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,258,1003]" box="[199,804,906,931]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,672,906,931]" pageId="22" pageNumber="285">Natural history and habitat preferences</emphasis>
